text:
The sourcecode for the JSP examples in the examples application of Tomcat is not

creator: remm@apache.org
text:
That's working fine for me.
I noticed that IE has the annoying habit of displaying stuff which vaguely 
looks like HTML as HTML, regardless of the content type. For example, looking 
at the source for the date example will do that. If you use "view source" you 
should see the real JSP source.
Is it what happened to you ?
